## Setting Up in a New Project

### 1. Add as submodule

```bash
git submodule add git@github.com:you/agent-stack.git .cursor/shared
git submodule update --init
```

### 2. Symlink into Cursor paths

```bash
ln -s shared/agents   .cursor/agents
ln -s shared/skills   .cursor/skills
ln -s shared/rules    .cursor/rules
ln -s shared/hooks    .cursor/hooks
ln -s shared/commands .cursor/commands
```

### 3. Git commit-msg hook

```bash
cp .cursor/shared/hooks/git/commit-msg-append-review.sh .git/hooks/commit-msg
chmod +x .git/hooks/commit-msg
```

### 4. Project context (optional)

Create `.cursor/project-context.md` in your project for project-specific overrides (not in the submodule). The stack-context rule is always loaded; project-context adds project-specific testing paths, Stryker config, etc.

---

## MCP Servers

Configure `.cursor/mcp.json` in your project for Supabase, Playwright, Figma (optional), Context7:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "supabase": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "-y",
        "@supabase/mcp-server-supabase@latest",
        "--supabase-url", "https://your-project.supabase.co",
        "--supabase-key", "${SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY}",
        "--features", "database,storage"
      ]
    },
    "playwright": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@playwright/mcp@latest"]
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Keeping Projects Up to Date

```bash
# In any project using agent-stack
git submodule update --remote --merge
```

Alias: `alias ai-sync="git submodule update --remote --merge"`

---

## Versioning

Tag stable states:

```bash
git tag -a v1.0.0 -m "stable: single-stack complete"
git push --tags
```

Pin a project to a version:

```bash
cd your-project
git -C .cursor/shared checkout v1.0.0
```
